         xml:id="Repose-Content-Normalization-Chapter">
    <title>Content Normalization</title>


    <section xml:id="Content-Normalization-Introduction">
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>
            Content normalization is the process of modifying or standardizing content to optimize the flow of
            information.
        </para>
        <para>
            The Content Normalization filter allows normalization of the headers and media-type of the request by
            performing
            three separate functions. The filter prevents specific requests from passing to the origin service using
            blacklisting,
            it passes only approved headers to the origin service using whitelisting, or it normalizes accept headers
            using media-typing.
        </para>
    </section>

    <section xml:id="Content-Normalization-use-cases" security="writeronly">
        <title>Content Normalization Use Cases</title>
